<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="105" type="sex association">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Sex association.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
The male of the type species has not been recognized; the presumed males of other species were associated and described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, AS" journalOrPublisher="Dalnauka, Vladivostok" pageId="15" pageNumber="118" title="Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region." year="2005">Lelej 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 196. The following pairs of species may eventually be recognized as opposite sexes: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia yamanei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamanei">Promecidia yamanei</taxonomicName>
Lelej, 1996, ♀, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia rubrocyanea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrocyanea">Promecidia rubrocyanea</taxonomicName>
(Mickel, 1935), ♂ (both are from Borneo, with dark metallic blue metasoma); 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia boopis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boopis">Promecidia boopis</taxonomicName>
(Kohl, 1882), ♀, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia bonthainensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonthainensis">Promecidia bonthainensis</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
, 1896), ♂ (both are from Sulawesi); 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia mamblia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamblia">Promecidia mamblia</taxonomicName>
(Cameron, 1902), ♀, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1996" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Promecidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Promecidia samawangensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samawangensis">Promecidia samawangensis</taxonomicName>
